      • getBuilderAddMethodName

        public String getBuilderAddMethodName()
        Used for builder testing / verifying: In case builderMethodPrefix is null the corresponding build method to be accessed for setting the value is the name attribute: PropertyMetadata.getName(), in case it is a concrete value, e.g. 'with' it will taken into account: withPropertName().

      • getBuilderSingleAddMethodName

        public String getBuilderSingleAddMethodName()
        Similar to BuilderMetadata.BuilderMetadataBuilder.builderMethodName(String) but for special cases described within PropertyAccessStrategy.BUILDER_COLLECTION_AND_SINGLE_ELEMENT There are two different steps for deriving the concrete method-name:
        • Base-name: In case BuilderMetadata.BuilderMetadataBuilder.builderSingleAddMethodName(String) is not set it used PropertyMetadata.getName() as base name -> Overloading
        • The base-name will prefixed if there is a builderPerfixed configured, see BuilderMetadata.BuilderMetadataBuilder.builderMethodPrefix(String)
